/*
Linked list(linear data structure):
it is a linear data structure, it is a collection of data elements, called nodes.
A node is a basic element of a linked list. it consists of data and the adress of the next node and forms a chain.asm

A linked list is formed when many such nodes are linked together to form a chain. Each node points to the next node present in the order. The
First node is always used as a reference to ransverse the list and is called HEAD. The last node points to NULL. 

HEAD:  1st node of the list OR  adress of 1st node of the list.
NULL: LAST ,, ,, ,, ,, ,, ,,.

NODE consists of two parts I.E DATA and NEXT POINTER.  
DATA: it is the part of node which stores the info in the linked list.
NEXT POINTER: it is the part of node which stores the address of the next node in the linked.

*/
